As for the proposed architecture, I would suggest a microservices-based approach, leveraging our expertise in containerization and orchestration using Kubernetes. This will allow us to deploy and manage multiple services, each responsible for a specific function, such as API integration, EDM system interaction, and user directory management. We can also utilize our experience with message brokers like Apache Kafka to handle communication between services.

To ensure high availability and scalability, we can design the architecture to include load balancing, auto-scaling, and redundancy, using cloud providers' built-in features or tools like Terraform for infrastructure-as-code management. Additionally, implementing monitoring and logging tools will enable us to quickly identify and respond to any issues that may arise, helping to meet the required availability and response time targets.

