We utilize anonymisation tools such as Microsoft Presidio and custom NER models to protect sensitive data. Additionally, we have implemented data subject rights including access, rectification, erasure, portability, and objection. We also conduct Data Protection Impact Assessments with an average duration of 3 weeks.

Furthermore, we enforce multi-factor authentication, utilize role-based access control design, and deploy Privileged Access Management solutions like CyberArk Conjur and HashiCorp Vault to limit access to sensitive data. Our network security architecture follows zero-trust, micro-segmentation, and defence-in-depth patterns, with intrusion detection and prevention systems deployed.

We also have experience in conducting regular penetration tests, at least annually and post-major releases, with the last test resulting in two medium findings that were remediated. For AI-powered information systems, we protect against prompt injection, redact personally identifiable information from outputs, detect adversarial inputs, and implement model isolation and security reviews for model updates.

Lastly, all queries are logged with immutability ensured through append-only logging with SHA-256 hash chaining, and logs are retained for 7 years. We integrate our logging with real-time Security Information and Event Management tools like Wazuh and Elastic SIEM.
