Additionally, we can offer to establish a data processing agreement based on our DPA template version 3.2, which relies on Article 6(1)(e) of the GDPR as the standard legal basis for processing. Since our operations are intra-EU only, no Standard Contractual Clauses or adequacy decisions are required, simplifying the compliance process.

Regarding potential risks and liabilities, Nexus Engineering S.r.l. has a limitation of liability set at 3,000,000 euros, professional indemnity insurance covering up to 5,000,000 euros, and cyber liability insurance for up to 2,000,000 euros. Our policy with AXA XL is valid until December 31, 2025.

It's also worth noting that we have a no-copyleft GPL contamination policy in place and use standard licenses such as Apache 2.0 and MIT, which are cleared for commercial use. Furthermore, our default IP model is work-for-hire, ensuring that all deliverables are transferred to the client upon final payment.

To mitigate risks associated with data sovereignty and regulatory compliance, we can propose regular audits and monitoring of our open-source license compliance, cross-border data flow (although this is intra-EU and thus not a significant concern), AI Act compliance evolution, and vendor lock-in mitigation strategies, including source code escrow with Logitas in France.
